# 3. Prerequisite: Binary Heap

A Binary Heap is a Complete Binary Tree.

Two Types:

## Max Heap

Parent is greater than children.

```text
        50
      /    \
    30      40
   /  \
 20   10
```

### Property

```text
Parent >= Children
```

---

## Min Heap

Parent is smaller than children.

```text
        10
      /    \
    20      30
   /  \
 40   50
```

### Property

```text
Parent <= Children
```

---

# 4. Array Representation of Heap

For index i:

```text
Parent = (i - 1) / 2

Left Child = 2*i + 1

Right Child = 2*i + 2
```

Example:

```text
Index: 0 1 2 3 4 5 6

Array: 50 30 40 10 20 35 25
```

Tree:

```text
          50
        /    \
      30      40
     /  \    /  \
   10   20 35   25
```

---

# 5. Heap Sort Idea

For Ascending Order:

```text
Build Max Heap

Largest element moves to root

Swap root with last element

Reduce heap size

Heapify root again

Repeat
```

