# 24. 10-Second Interview Answer

"Heap Sort is an in-place comparison-based sorting algorithm that uses a Binary Heap. For ascending order, it first builds a Max Heap, then repeatedly swaps the root with the last element, reduces the heap size, and heapifies the root. It guarantees O(n log n) time complexity in all cases and requires O(1) extra space, but it is not stable."
